<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-974] RequestWrapper does not use the headers of the request it wraps.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-974</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>The RequestWrapper does not use the headers of the request it wraps. Therefore the wrapper appears as having no header, while the wrapped request may have some.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
To work-around that behavior, I have to call resetHeaders() on the wrapper just after having created it.&lt;br/&gt;
This method does the following:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;public void resetHeaders()&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;{&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;headergroup.clear();&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;setHeaders(original.getAllHeaders());&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;}&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I suggest calling setHeaders directly in the constructor. Or at least highlight in the Javadoc that we should call resetHeaders().</description>
